WEBVTT

00:01.919 --> 00:02.376
(tense music)

01:35.805 --> 01:38.222
(soft music)

01:47.650 --> 01:48.899
- Hi, handsome.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.109
- Good morning, gorgeous.

01:56.117 --> 01:56.990
Lauren: Morning.

01:57.034 --> 01:58.242
- There they are.

01:58.285 --> 01:59.243
- Morning, Dad.

01:59.286 --> 02:00.494
- Hi.

02:00.538 --> 02:01.453
- Morning.
- Good morning, Dad.

02:01.497 --> 02:01.954
- Morning, sweetie.

02:01.997 --> 02:03.455
- Thank you.

02:03.499 --> 02:03.997
- Good morning, Dad.
- Good morning, son.

02:07.336 --> 02:08.293
- Bye, guys, love ya.

02:08.336 --> 02:09.919
- Bye.
- Bye, have a good day.

02:09.964 --> 02:12.464
- Oh, don't forget to come
home right after school today.

02:12.508 --> 02:13.757
- (scoffs) We know, you told us,

02:13.801 --> 02:15.926
like, a million
times. (chuckles)

02:15.970 --> 02:16.718
- Did I?

02:16.762 --> 02:18.428
- Yeah.

02:18.472 --> 02:21.056
- Okay, come home
right after school.

02:22.476 --> 02:23.267
- Later.

02:26.313 --> 02:27.187
- You nervous?

02:28.774 --> 02:30.399
- I just can't believe
this is actually happening.

02:31.527 --> 02:33.152
It's all so sudden.

02:33.195 --> 02:35.696
- I know, but it was
the right thing to do.

02:35.739 --> 02:37.865
- I haven't seen
Samantha in years.

02:37.908 --> 02:40.409
Jeez, it's been decades.

02:40.452 --> 02:42.119
She was only a year
old when I left.

02:42.163 --> 02:44.288
- Hey, none of
this is your fault.

02:46.750 --> 02:51.086
- I know, I just feel like
I could've tried harder.

02:51.130 --> 02:53.463
- Samantha's mother cut
you out of her life.

02:53.507 --> 02:56.049
You did the best you could
under the circumstances,

02:56.093 --> 02:58.260
and now you're making it right.

02:58.304 --> 02:59.094
- Yeah.

03:00.556 --> 03:02.014
- You still nervous?

03:02.057 --> 03:03.348
- Of course.

03:03.392 --> 03:04.850
What if she doesn't like me?

03:04.894 --> 03:06.393
- Who wouldn't love you?

03:06.437 --> 03:08.979
- Cats, cats do not love me.

03:09.023 --> 03:10.480
Maybe small birds,

03:10.524 --> 03:12.024
and that guy that works
at the liquor store, he--

03:12.067 --> 03:13.358
- Greg, you're gonna be fine.

03:14.653 --> 03:16.570
Look, this is your
second chance,

03:16.614 --> 03:18.822
you deserve to know Samantha.

03:20.326 --> 03:21.450
You can do this.

03:21.493 --> 03:23.285
We can totally do this.

03:25.748 --> 03:27.581
- How'd I get so lucky?

03:27.625 --> 03:28.457
- Oh.

03:31.462 --> 03:34.171
- Oh, hey, what do you think
Samantha might want for dinner?

03:34.215 --> 03:37.216
- Well, she told me she's
a vegetarian, so, lettuce?

03:38.677 --> 03:41.094
- I can work with that.
(soft music)

03:41.138 --> 03:42.429
- You have any clients today?

03:42.473 --> 03:46.600
- No, I took the whole
day off to prepare.

03:46.644 --> 03:49.478
- Well, I only have
two consults, so...

03:49.521 --> 03:50.562
- No surgeries? I
don't believe it.

03:50.606 --> 03:52.814
- Believe it, baby.

03:52.858 --> 03:54.942
I might actually be
home early for once.

03:54.985 --> 03:55.901
- That'll be the day.

03:55.945 --> 03:56.777
- Love you.

03:56.820 --> 03:58.070
- Love you too.

04:00.532 --> 04:04.284
(doorbell rings)

04:04.328 --> 04:07.287
- Samantha, it's
so good to see you.

04:08.332 --> 04:11.250
- Hey, Dad. (chuckles)

04:11.293 --> 04:13.293
- Uh, hi, I'm Katie.

04:13.337 --> 04:16.296
Uh, these are your
half-siblings,

04:16.339 --> 04:18.048
this is Lauren and Tommy.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.548
- Hey.

04:19.593 --> 04:21.260
- It's so nice to
meet you, Samantha.

04:23.222 --> 04:24.388
Katie: Oh, come in,
come in, please.

04:24.431 --> 04:25.847
- Uh, I--

04:25.891 --> 04:26.473
Katie: Tommy, will you
help her with her bags?

04:26.517 --> 04:27.557
- Yeah, of course.

04:28.852 --> 04:30.477
Katie: Ah, so are you hungry?

04:30.521 --> 04:31.937
Greg said you're a vegetarian?

04:31.981 --> 04:33.647
- Yeah, I'm definitely hungry.

04:33.691 --> 04:36.024
Katie: All right,
how was your trip?

04:36.068 --> 04:37.776
- Uh, it was okay,
it was uneventful.

04:40.489 --> 04:41.613
Greg: Oh.
(Katie chuckles)

04:41.657 --> 04:43.448
- So how did you guys meet?

04:43.492 --> 04:46.535
- Um...
- Uh, well,

04:46.578 --> 04:48.120
I was working--
- That's going way back.

04:48.163 --> 04:51.081
- Yeah, I was working at this
coffee shop, near campus,

04:51.125 --> 04:54.418
and Greg would come in
every Wednesday morning,

04:54.461 --> 04:55.836
that was my shift.

04:55.879 --> 04:57.546
One day, he finally
asked me out,

04:57.589 --> 04:59.673
and he was so excited

04:59.717 --> 05:00.841
that I had said yes
(Greg chuckles)

05:00.884 --> 05:03.093
on the first ask,

05:03.137 --> 05:05.512
that he's walking
away from me all cool

05:05.556 --> 05:07.222
and maintaining eye contact,

05:07.266 --> 05:08.515
and he fell and tripped

05:08.559 --> 05:10.600
and got stuck in the bush
(Greg chuckles)

05:10.644 --> 05:11.768
and I had to help him out.

05:11.812 --> 05:13.270
I've never laughed
so hard in my life,

05:13.314 --> 05:15.897
his arms and legs flailing
all over the place,

05:15.941 --> 05:17.232
it was so good.
- Okay,

05:17.276 --> 05:18.358
they weren't flailing,
(Samantha laughs)

05:18.402 --> 05:19.901
that's a bit of an exaggeration.

05:19.945 --> 05:22.154
- Well, how long have
you guys been married?

05:23.532 --> 05:26.325
- Uh, it'll be 19
years next month.

05:26.368 --> 05:28.452
- Wow, 19 years.

05:28.495 --> 05:29.911
Congratulations.

05:29.955 --> 05:31.872
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.291
- I guess it didn't take you
long to start a new family

05:34.335 --> 05:36.209
after Mom kicked you out?

05:36.253 --> 05:39.087
(tense music)

05:39.131 --> 05:42.674
- Listen, Sam, I wanted
to be a part of your life,

05:42.718 --> 05:46.303
I always wanted that, but
your Mother, she just refused.

05:46.347 --> 05:48.847
- Don't worry, Dad,
I get how she was.

05:50.601 --> 05:52.684
Um, I'm kinda tired.

05:54.563 --> 05:55.520
- You must be.

05:55.564 --> 05:57.814
Uh, Lauren, Tommy,

05:57.858 --> 05:59.608
do you guys wanna
help Sam get settled

05:59.651 --> 06:01.151
and show her to her room?

06:01.195 --> 06:03.612
- Uh, we can give you a
quick tour if you'd like,

06:03.655 --> 06:05.447
show you around in
case you need anything.

06:05.491 --> 06:06.823
- Okay, sure.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.033
- Right this way.

06:08.077 --> 06:10.035
(Samantha and Lauren chuckle)

06:10.079 --> 06:11.870
- Oh, I'll help you with these.

06:19.380 --> 06:20.796
- And this is your room.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.925
Bathroom's right
there, I'm next door,

06:24.968 --> 06:27.469
and Tommy's just
upstairs if you need us.

06:27.513 --> 06:29.763
- Cool, thanks so much for
helping me with my bags,

06:29.807 --> 06:31.681
and it's so nice
to meet you guys.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.475
- You too.

06:33.519 --> 06:35.811
I'm really sorry about your mom,

06:35.854 --> 06:38.313
but I'm really glad
that you're here.

06:40.526 --> 06:41.358
- Thanks.

06:43.070 --> 06:44.611
- So,

06:44.655 --> 06:48.782
uh, do you go by
Sam or Samantha?

06:48.826 --> 06:50.534
- Yeah, Sam's fine. (chuckles)

06:50.577 --> 06:51.368
- Cool.

06:52.663 --> 06:53.787
Well, goodnight, Sam.

06:53.831 --> 06:55.372
- Goodnight.
- Night, sweet dreams.

06:55.416 --> 06:56.164
- You too.

07:00.254 --> 07:01.044
(knock at door)

07:01.088 --> 07:01.795
- Oh, come in.

07:07.511 --> 07:08.635
- You need anything?

07:08.679 --> 07:10.095
- Uh, no, I'm good,

07:10.139 --> 07:12.556
I think I'm just gonna
unpack a bit before bed.

07:15.727 --> 07:16.518
- Um...

07:18.230 --> 07:20.856
I'm, I'm really happy
that this all worked out.

07:22.609 --> 07:23.775
- Yeah, me too.

07:25.654 --> 07:28.947
- Oh, also, only if
you're feeling up to it,

07:28.991 --> 07:32.576
tomorrow night, my
boss is throwing this
little get-together

07:32.619 --> 07:34.744
for my work anniversary.

07:34.788 --> 07:37.998
He lives right next door,
it's just nothing fancy,

07:38.041 --> 07:40.625
some family friends
and colleagues.

07:42.588 --> 07:45.839
- Yeah, um, it sounds great.

07:45.883 --> 07:48.175
- Great.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.342
Great, all right, well,

07:50.512 --> 07:51.928
goodnight, Samantha.

07:51.972 --> 07:55.390
- Hey, Dad, um, (sighs)

07:57.269 --> 07:59.019
thanks so much for having me,

08:00.689 --> 08:01.605
I really missed you.

08:10.699 --> 08:11.656
- Sweet dreams.

08:11.700 --> 08:13.408
Samantha: Night.

08:20.083 --> 08:22.667
(tense music)

08:27.174 --> 08:29.674
- You know, I think
that went really well.

08:29.718 --> 08:31.259
- Yeah.

08:31.303 --> 08:32.302
She seems sweet.

08:33.722 --> 08:35.514
God, what happened to
her mom was so tragic.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.976
You know, I could try to talk
to her, get her to open up.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.979
- Oh, don't do that.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.065
Not yet, I really want her
to feel comfortable here.

08:45.108 --> 08:46.858
- Yeah, I want that too,

08:46.902 --> 08:49.069
I just know that healing
requires letting it out,

08:50.489 --> 08:52.280
and she also seemed
pretty uncomfortable

08:52.324 --> 08:55.075
when we were talking
about our relationship.

08:55.118 --> 08:56.117
- She didn't mean it.

08:57.496 --> 08:59.788
I mean, it's a lot for
anybody to take in.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.415
- You're right,
no, you're right,

09:02.459 --> 09:05.252
I'm sure it's just my therapist
brain working overtime.

09:07.047 --> 09:10.632
- Let's not psychoanalyze her
before getting to know her,

09:10.676 --> 09:11.841
deal?

09:11.885 --> 09:12.676
- Deal.

09:14.680 --> 09:18.098
How are you feeling
with all of this?

09:19.351 --> 09:21.977
- I see, psychoanalyzing
me now, Doctor.

09:22.020 --> 09:23.770
- Shut up.

09:23.814 --> 09:25.438
- Uh, I'm excited,

09:26.525 --> 09:27.315
I'm scared,

09:28.485 --> 09:30.986
and I don't know what I'm doing.

09:31.029 --> 09:34.447
- You don't have to, we're
gonna do it together.

09:39.204 --> 09:40.328
- Get in here.

09:42.332 --> 09:44.874
(upbeat music))

09:48.422 --> 09:51.423
(indistinct chatter)

09:52.926 --> 09:56.595
- Thank you for coming
today, it's an honor.

09:57.556 --> 09:59.389
Excuse me for a moment.

10:01.435 --> 10:03.685
- That's, that does help.

10:03.729 --> 10:04.477
It does help.

10:04.521 --> 10:05.770
Hi, oh, hello.

10:06.648 --> 10:07.856
- Plastic surgery?

10:07.899 --> 10:09.816
- Not easy, I know.
- Greg, hi.

10:09.860 --> 10:10.775
- Hi.

10:10.819 --> 10:11.985
- How are you doing?

10:12.029 --> 10:14.029
- Good, tough to
follow in my footsteps,

10:14.072 --> 10:15.488
(drowned out).

10:15.532 --> 10:17.741
Tommy: Dad, I'd love to
be a plastic surgeon.

10:18.577 --> 10:20.869
(clinks glass)

10:20.912 --> 10:23.747
- I'd, uh, like to
propose a toast.

10:26.001 --> 10:30.462
Dr. Greg Carlisle is the
epitome of everything

10:30.505 --> 10:33.548
that Saint Joseph's
Hospital strives to be.

10:35.844 --> 10:36.843
Kind,

10:37.971 --> 10:39.179
family-oriented,

10:40.641 --> 10:43.558
and committed to
providing our community

10:43.602 --> 10:46.519
with the best possible care.

10:46.563 --> 10:49.898
He is the definition
of grounded,

10:51.401 --> 10:55.320
has raised two beautiful
children, Tommy and Lauren,

10:57.115 --> 11:00.742
and, uh, married a woman
who I must say is, um,

11:02.079 --> 11:03.828
way out of his
league. (laughter)

11:03.872 --> 11:04.871
Am I right?

11:04.915 --> 11:05.705
Greg: Yes, sure.

11:05.749 --> 11:07.040
- Ladies and gentlemen,

11:07.084 --> 11:08.875
Greg Carlisle and
his beautiful family.

11:09.878 --> 11:12.128
(glasses clink)

11:12.172 --> 11:13.755
Yeah, come on, don't be shy.

11:14.966 --> 11:16.591
- Well, thank you, Richard.

11:16.635 --> 11:17.384
- You're welcome.

11:19.221 --> 11:22.639
- It's an honor to be a part
of the Saint Joseph's team,

11:22.683 --> 11:27.435
and I'm very grateful for
the incredible support staff,

11:29.606 --> 11:31.022
and I'm so happy
that so many of you

11:31.066 --> 11:32.482
were able to be here tonight.

11:33.944 --> 11:37.028
My work is as important to me

11:37.072 --> 11:39.823
as being a father and a husband,

11:41.660 --> 11:44.202
and as my beautiful wife says,

11:44.246 --> 11:46.705
being Superman only takes
the will to try, so...

11:49.209 --> 11:52.585
So thank you for allowing
me the opportunity

11:52.629 --> 11:54.879
to make a difference in the
lives of this community.

11:57.592 --> 11:59.467
Man: Woo! Here-here!

11:59.511 --> 12:01.845
(upbeat music)

12:08.895 --> 12:11.896
(indistinct chatter)

12:13.108 --> 12:13.857
- Samantha?

12:16.194 --> 12:17.026
Samantha?

12:18.613 --> 12:19.404
Samantha?

12:21.074 --> 12:22.532
Samantha, wait.

12:22.576 --> 12:23.575
He didn't mean it.

12:23.618 --> 12:24.826
- He didn't even mention me.

12:24.870 --> 12:26.536
- He didn't know.

12:26.580 --> 12:28.955
Now, look, this is a new
situation for all of us, okay?

12:28.999 --> 12:30.665
We just need a
chance to acclimate.

12:30.709 --> 12:32.250
- It is all about your
perfect-family image,

12:32.294 --> 12:34.252
I just don't fit in.

12:34.296 --> 12:36.838
- Of course you do,
this is your family now.

12:36.882 --> 12:38.840
- No, it's not.

12:38.884 --> 12:39.591
- Samantha--

12:39.634 --> 12:40.425
- Don't.

12:50.937 --> 12:53.480
(tense music)

12:55.484 --> 12:57.942
(door opens)

13:00.739 --> 13:02.030
- Hey.

13:02.073 --> 13:02.864
- Hey.

13:04.534 --> 13:07.076
So, does everyone hate me now?

13:07.954 --> 13:09.078
- What?

13:09.122 --> 13:10.538
No, no one hates you.

13:11.875 --> 13:14.000
- Yeah, right. (scoffs)

13:16.463 --> 13:17.212
- You know, I was
just thinking about

13:17.255 --> 13:19.464
my favorite memory of you.

13:19.508 --> 13:22.050
I came to visit, and we all
went out for Italian food,

13:22.093 --> 13:24.928
and I bought you this
big, pink, stuffed bear.

13:24.971 --> 13:26.387
It was bigger than you.

13:26.431 --> 13:28.014
- (chuckles) I
remember that bear.

13:28.058 --> 13:29.766
- Yeah, and you were
wearing these overalls

13:29.810 --> 13:31.392
with these little
balloons on the front.

13:31.436 --> 13:33.478
We tried to keep them clean,

13:33.522 --> 13:36.022
but you kept getting
spaghetti all over them.

13:36.066 --> 13:37.816
And I sat next to you,

13:37.859 --> 13:40.276
and you fed me pasta with
your grubby little hands.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.822
- You mean I wasn't even
using a napkin and a fork yet?

13:43.865 --> 13:46.199
- Nope, you took after your
dad right from the start.

13:48.119 --> 13:49.953
- I wish it had just
been you and me.

13:51.748 --> 13:52.831
- Well, now it can be.

13:54.209 --> 13:55.583
Just give it a
little time, okay?

13:57.087 --> 13:58.461
Katie's great, and the kids.

13:59.840 --> 14:01.339
You'll see once you
get to know them.

14:02.467 --> 14:05.301
And if you feel up to it,

14:05.345 --> 14:07.136
you can go with them to
Tommy's soccer game tomorrow,

14:07.180 --> 14:09.389
it'll be fun.
(Samantha chuckles)

14:09.432 --> 14:11.015
- All right, I'll go.

14:11.059 --> 14:13.017
- Great, I'll tell Katie.

14:13.061 --> 14:14.102
- Hey, Dad?

14:14.145 --> 14:14.894
- Yeah?

14:16.648 --> 14:18.356
- I'll always be
your favorite, right?

14:22.821 --> 14:23.611
- You're my girl.

14:29.744 --> 14:32.078
(tense music)

14:38.128 --> 14:40.461
(alarm rings)

14:45.176 --> 14:47.802
(tense music)

14:53.143 --> 14:55.602
(floor creaks)

15:42.317 --> 15:44.067
- Uh, oh.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.902
Uh, (chuckles) you scared me.

15:47.280 --> 15:48.863
I thought you were
still sleeping.

15:48.907 --> 15:51.783
- No, I, I was just
looking for something.

15:53.244 --> 15:54.494
- Anything in particular?

15:56.581 --> 15:58.247
- Yeah, do you have tape?

15:59.334 --> 16:01.417
- Yeah, uh, it's
right here actually.

16:09.094 --> 16:09.801
- Thanks.

16:09.886 --> 16:10.677
- Mm-hmm.

16:10.720 --> 16:13.388
(tense music)

16:13.431 --> 16:16.265
(doorbell rings)

16:36.579 --> 16:37.662
- Much better.

16:56.975 --> 16:58.850
- All right, come on, Tommy!
- Let's go, let's go.

16:58.893 --> 17:00.059
- Let's go!

17:00.103 --> 17:01.310
Come on, Tommy!

17:06.192 --> 17:09.694
- I'm gonna apply to 12
schools, three Ivy League.

17:09.738 --> 17:12.238
I'd love to go to Brown,
that's where you go, right?

17:12.281 --> 17:14.156
- Yeah, I'm taking
the semester off.

17:14.200 --> 17:15.241
- Oh, what's your major?

17:15.285 --> 17:16.701
- Psyche.

17:16.744 --> 17:18.703
Mom wanted me to major
in business, but...

17:20.874 --> 17:21.914
- Yeah!
- Yeah! (crowd cheers)

17:21.958 --> 17:23.415
Yeah!

17:23.460 --> 17:24.375
- Nice one!

17:24.419 --> 17:25.376
- Woo!
- Woo!

17:34.054 --> 17:35.636
- Hey, Lauren.

17:35.680 --> 17:36.471
- Hey, Milo.

17:39.934 --> 17:41.142
- Oh,

17:41.186 --> 17:42.143
Milo.

17:43.229 --> 17:45.354
So, what's the story?

17:46.316 --> 17:47.356
- What story?

17:48.777 --> 17:51.110
- Listen, Miss Innocent,
I can tell you like him.

17:51.154 --> 17:52.445
- It's nothing.

17:53.364 --> 17:54.906
He's a senior anyway, so--

17:54.949 --> 17:55.740
- So?

17:57.077 --> 17:59.327
- I mean, (chuckles)
I've never really, like,

17:59.370 --> 18:00.703
been with a guy
or anything, so--

18:00.747 --> 18:02.163
- Like, not even kissed?

18:02.207 --> 18:02.955
(Lauren chuckles)

18:02.999 --> 18:04.332
I mean, come on.

18:04.375 --> 18:06.709
- Nope, not even kissed.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.669
- Well, we will fix that.

18:18.807 --> 18:19.972
- So, uh,

18:21.017 --> 18:21.849
she cool?

18:23.645 --> 18:26.312
- She seems nice, I haven't
really hung out with her yet.

18:26.356 --> 18:28.564
- Hey, it sucks what
happened to her, man.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.608
Hey, she talk about it yet?

18:30.652 --> 18:33.694
- Nah, man, I think she
wants to forget all that.

18:33.738 --> 18:34.529
- Oh.

18:35.907 --> 18:36.614
- She's hot.

18:37.784 --> 18:39.033
- Samantha looks like

18:39.077 --> 18:40.034
she's getting along
well with everyone.

18:40.078 --> 18:41.119
How's that transition going?

18:41.162 --> 18:42.995
- Yeah, yeah, you know,

18:43.039 --> 18:44.288
I mean, it's only
been a couple of days,

18:44.332 --> 18:46.833
but the way she's getting
along with the kids,

18:46.876 --> 18:49.085
I mean, so far, so good.

18:49.129 --> 18:50.795
- Good.
- Seems promising.

18:50.839 --> 18:51.587
- Good.

18:53.800 --> 18:55.216
- I'm gonna be right back, guys.

18:57.720 --> 18:58.469
- This guy.

19:00.348 --> 19:02.223
- So, can I sit
down with you guys?

19:03.560 --> 19:04.350
- Yeah.

19:08.022 --> 19:09.939
- So you gonna introduce
me to your friend?

19:09.983 --> 19:11.023
- Oh, uh, this is--

19:11.067 --> 19:12.567
- I'm Samantha.

19:12.610 --> 19:14.152
I'm Lauren's sister.

19:14.195 --> 19:15.945
Well, technically, I'm
only her half-sister,

19:15.989 --> 19:18.531
but we are working on being
one big, happy family,

19:18.575 --> 19:19.615
right, sis?

19:19.659 --> 19:20.992
- Yeah, (chuckles) totally.

19:21.035 --> 19:22.160
- Cool.

19:22.203 --> 19:23.828
So what are you, like, a junior?

19:25.081 --> 19:27.165
- Yeah, in college.

19:27.208 --> 19:29.917
You look like you could
be a college boy yourself.

19:29.961 --> 19:31.669
- Oh, yeah? Thanks.

19:31.713 --> 19:35.089
I was thinking Notre
Dame, Coach Academy.

19:35.133 --> 19:37.758
(Lauren chuckles)
- Oh, you mean Notre Dame.

19:37.802 --> 19:38.593
- Notre Dame.

19:40.638 --> 19:42.805
- My dad said not to ask
any questions, all right?

19:44.142 --> 19:45.850
Her mom was in the house
when it burned down.

19:45.894 --> 19:47.768
- (scoffs) More like exploded.

19:47.812 --> 19:49.187
Like, I looked it up, man.

19:51.024 --> 19:52.356
Look, there was nothing left

19:52.400 --> 19:54.025
by the time the fire
department got there.

19:55.486 --> 19:56.652
- All right, well, I'm sure
the last thing she wants

19:56.696 --> 19:57.820
is everyone feeling bad for her,

19:57.864 --> 20:00.656
so just be cool with her,

20:00.700 --> 20:02.825
don't ask any questions.

20:02.869 --> 20:04.869
- I'm gonna get something to
drink, can I get you something?

20:05.788 --> 20:06.787
- Sure.
- Cool.

20:06.831 --> 20:07.747
I'll be right back.

20:14.047 --> 20:15.922
- What is up with you?

20:15.965 --> 20:17.006
- Nothing.

20:17.967 --> 20:19.800
- Come on, tell me.

20:21.721 --> 20:22.929
- You were flirting with him.

20:24.182 --> 20:24.931
- With who?

20:26.059 --> 20:27.892
- Milo. (chuckles)

20:27.936 --> 20:29.810
- What, that?

20:29.854 --> 20:33.064
No, oh, my gosh, don't
be jealous, I was
doing that for you.

20:33.107 --> 20:35.107
It's all a part of my
Lauren and Milo plan,

20:35.151 --> 20:36.359
I promise, trust me.

20:38.196 --> 20:38.945
Yes.

20:41.115 --> 20:41.822
Who's that?

20:43.785 --> 20:45.159
- Ryan?

20:45.203 --> 20:47.495
He's Tommy's soccer coach.

20:47.538 --> 20:49.956
Him and my mom have known each
other since, like, forever.

20:51.376 --> 20:52.541
- And Dad's cool with it?

20:54.003 --> 20:54.961
- I mean, yeah.

20:56.089 --> 20:58.089
I guess, I don't know, why?

20:59.926 --> 21:02.218
- No reason, I'm just gonna
go over and introduce myself.

21:05.014 --> 21:05.972
- Here you go.

21:06.015 --> 21:06.806
- Thanks.

21:09.018 --> 21:09.934
- Where's she going?

21:11.479 --> 21:14.397
- Oh, she's just gonna
introduce herself to Ryan.

21:14.440 --> 21:15.314
Samantha: Hey, Katie.

21:15.358 --> 21:16.482
- Oh, hey, Samantha.

21:16.526 --> 21:17.775
You having a good time?

21:17.819 --> 21:20.111
- Yeah, totally.

21:20.154 --> 21:21.487
Um, wait, I'm Samantha.
- Oh, this is, um...

21:21.531 --> 21:22.446
Sorry.
- Ryan,

21:22.490 --> 21:24.907
it's nice to finally meet you.

21:24.951 --> 21:27.118
- So how do you guys
know each other?

21:27.161 --> 21:29.203
- Oh, well, I met Katie
when we were kids,

21:29.247 --> 21:30.162
we grew up together.

21:31.040 --> 21:32.957
- Did you date?

21:33.001 --> 21:35.918
- No. (chuckles)
- No, uh, just friends.

21:35.962 --> 21:37.253
Since, what, eighth grade?

21:37.297 --> 21:39.380
- No, no, it was
seventh, remember?

21:39.424 --> 21:40.881
Because it was Mrs.
Parker's class. (chuckles)

21:40.925 --> 21:43.175
- Yeah, (chuckles) friends.

21:44.929 --> 21:47.221
- My son, Trevor, and Tommy,
they're on the team together.

21:47.265 --> 21:48.639
They've been best friends
since, what, elementary school?

21:48.683 --> 21:50.558
- Yeah.
- Oh, where's your wife?

21:50.601 --> 21:52.143
- Samantha.

21:52.186 --> 21:55.730
- Uh, it's okay, uh, my
wife died two years ago.

21:55.773 --> 21:58.232
Um, it was tough being
alone with Trevor,

21:58.276 --> 22:01.277
but Katie was really my
rock during that time,

22:01.321 --> 22:04.488
and I'm as grateful to her
and to your dad as I can be.

22:06.367 --> 22:09.243
- So what else do you
do besides coach soccer?

22:09.287 --> 22:12.580
- I'm a mechanic, I have my
own shop over on Brewer Street.

22:12.623 --> 22:15.041
- That is so cool, I
actually love cars.

22:16.210 --> 22:17.960
- You should stop by sometime.

22:18.004 --> 22:20.379
- Well, maybe
Katie will take me.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.342
- Sure, yeah, we
can figure it out.

22:25.261 --> 22:26.886
- Oh, Sam, pizza.

22:26.929 --> 22:28.304
- Well, pizza calls.

22:28.348 --> 22:30.306
Um, it was so nice
to meet you, Ryan.

22:30.350 --> 22:31.432
- Nice to meet you too.

22:49.118 --> 22:52.078
(car horn honks)

22:52.121 --> 22:54.288
- No way, no way,
are you kidding?

22:54.332 --> 22:56.207
You guys got me a car? What?

22:56.250 --> 22:57.625
- Passed your
driver's test, right?

22:57.668 --> 22:59.168
- Yeah, with flying colors,

22:59.212 --> 23:01.170
but I mean, I didn't
expect, like, a car.

23:01.214 --> 23:02.838
Did you know about this?

23:02.882 --> 23:03.964
- Well, I couldn't have you
keep asking 'em to drive mine,

23:04.008 --> 23:05.257
now could I?

23:05.301 --> 23:06.550
- We didn't know
about the color, but--

23:06.594 --> 23:08.469
- No, Mom, please, I
love it, I love it.

23:08.513 --> 23:10.221
Can I go see Trevor?

23:10.264 --> 23:12.848
- Uh, yeah, that's fine,
but please be home by 10,

23:12.892 --> 23:13.641
it is a school night.

23:13.684 --> 23:15.226
- Well, I wanna go too.

23:15.269 --> 23:16.852
- Come on, let's
break this bad boy in.

23:19.732 --> 23:21.273
- Aww, look at that.
(starts car)

23:21.317 --> 23:22.191
- So sweet.

23:22.235 --> 23:24.110
- So cute.
- Bye.

23:24.153 --> 23:27.405
- Don't crash it.
(Katie chuckles)

23:29.992 --> 23:30.866
- Where's my car?

23:32.578 --> 23:33.911
(tense music)

23:33.955 --> 23:35.371
- What do you mean
where's my car?

23:37.125 --> 23:39.750
- Tommy has a car, Lauren
has a car, where's mine?

23:42.547 --> 23:45.548
- Well, Tommy worked
really hard for his car,

23:45.591 --> 23:48.134
and Lauren got straight
A's for three years, and--

23:48.177 --> 23:49.593
- I wasn't talking to you.

23:51.013 --> 23:53.180
I thought that you
said I was special?

23:54.684 --> 23:56.058
- You are special.

23:56.102 --> 23:57.893
- Then why am I
being left out again?

23:59.730 --> 24:01.856
- Look, I know I wasn't there
when you got your license,

24:01.899 --> 24:04.108
and I'm really sorry about that,

24:04.152 --> 24:06.235
but, today's about Tommy,

24:06.279 --> 24:08.237
maybe we could just
cool it a little bit

24:08.281 --> 24:09.155
and talk about it...

24:09.198 --> 24:11.407
(kicks trunk)

24:11.451 --> 24:13.868
- So, everybody gets a fancy car

24:13.911 --> 24:16.662
and I get, what, a pink bear?

24:16.706 --> 24:19.457
I really see where I
fit into this family.

24:19.500 --> 24:21.250
Sorry, maybe Ryan can fix that,

24:21.294 --> 24:23.127
I heard he's good
with his hands.

24:31.304 --> 24:33.095
- That was something.

24:33.139 --> 24:34.430
I hate to say it, babe,

24:34.474 --> 24:36.515
but I'm a little
concerned about Sam.

24:36.559 --> 24:40.728
Jealousy's normal in these
types of new family situations,

24:40.771 --> 24:43.314
but her reactions have
been a little extreme.

24:46.486 --> 24:48.652
- We should get her a car too.

24:48.696 --> 24:51.864
- No, no, no, no, this has
nothing to do with a car,

24:51.908 --> 24:55.326
her jealousy stems
from insecurity

24:55.369 --> 24:58.245
and desperation
for your attention.

24:58.289 --> 25:00.080
Maybe this wasn't the best
time to get Tommy a new car,

25:00.124 --> 25:01.665
but it's done,

25:01.709 --> 25:03.542
now we need to focus on

25:03.586 --> 25:07.588
giving her a greater sense
of security and stability.

25:08.925 --> 25:10.549
- Yeah,

25:10.593 --> 25:11.926
I didn't even think about
how it would make her feel.

25:11.969 --> 25:14.220
I mean, I did miss
her entire childhood.

25:15.431 --> 25:16.639
- I understand that,

25:18.059 --> 25:19.975
but she can't go
around breaking things

25:20.019 --> 25:21.977
every time she gets angry.

25:22.021 --> 25:24.688
And we certainly
cannot reinforce that
behavior with a car.

25:26.734 --> 25:28.234
- You're right.

25:28.277 --> 25:29.443
You're right, I'm sorry.

25:30.363 --> 25:32.321
It's just a lot to take on,

25:32.365 --> 25:33.322
- I know, honey.

25:33.366 --> 25:34.657
- but I have to face it head on.

25:37.453 --> 25:38.619
I'm sorry about your car.

25:38.663 --> 25:39.995
- (chuckles) It's fine.

25:40.039 --> 25:41.413
- You want me to
make it up to you?

25:41.457 --> 25:43.374
(Katie chuckles)

25:43.417 --> 25:44.667
- You're incorrigible.

25:44.710 --> 25:45.626
- You mean insatiable.

25:45.670 --> 25:46.460
- Oh.

25:48.297 --> 25:49.380
- I'll go talk to her.

25:49.423 --> 25:50.381
- Thank you.

26:05.481 --> 26:08.023
(tense music)

26:17.118 --> 26:18.367
- Maybe I should take
one more day off?

26:18.411 --> 26:20.077
- No, we talked about
this last night.

26:20.121 --> 26:21.495
This will give me and Sam

26:21.539 --> 26:23.706
a better chance to get
to know one another.

26:23.749 --> 26:26.250
Plus, I know you're dying
to get back to the hospital.

26:26.294 --> 26:27.334
- You sure?

26:27.378 --> 26:28.294
- I'm sure.

26:28.337 --> 26:29.336
- All right.

26:31.674 --> 26:32.548
Good morning.

26:32.592 --> 26:33.299
- Hey.
- Morning.

26:33.342 --> 26:35.134
- Morning.

26:35.177 --> 26:36.635
- All right, I gotta go to
work, I'll see you guys.

26:36.679 --> 26:37.595
- Love you.
- Bye.

26:37.638 --> 26:38.971
- I love you.
- Love you.

26:39.015 --> 26:41.181
What's got you so
bouncy this morning?

26:41.225 --> 26:42.850
- Nothing, just happy.

26:42.893 --> 26:44.351
Katie: That's good.

26:44.395 --> 26:45.561
- Ah, morning, Sam.

26:45.605 --> 26:46.312
- Morning.
- Morning.

26:46.355 --> 26:48.147
Katie: Morning, Sam.

26:48.190 --> 26:49.857
- Hey, uh, Sam,

26:49.900 --> 26:51.567
couple of the guys from the
team are getting together later,

26:51.611 --> 26:52.776
if you wanna join?

26:52.820 --> 26:54.445
- Yeah, that sounds great.

26:54.488 --> 26:56.238
Lauren,

26:56.282 --> 26:59.533
you should come and put in
some time with you know who.

26:59.577 --> 27:01.410
Lauren: Oh, yeah,
sure. (chuckles)

27:01.454 --> 27:02.328
- Who's you know who?

27:02.371 --> 27:03.829
- Mom, it's nothing.

27:03.873 --> 27:05.247
- Milo Venetta.

27:05.291 --> 27:06.040
- (sighs) Sam.

27:06.083 --> 27:07.916
- Uh, gross.

27:07.960 --> 27:08.667
You like Milo?

27:08.711 --> 27:09.918
- Tommy.

27:09.962 --> 27:10.878
Stop.

27:10.921 --> 27:12.713
- Whatever floats your boat.

27:12.757 --> 27:13.881
- Bye, Sam.

27:13.924 --> 27:14.923
Samantha: Later.

27:14.967 --> 27:16.342
- Bye.
- Bye, have a good day.

27:18.679 --> 27:20.220
How'd you sleep last night?

27:20.264 --> 27:21.138
- Like a rock. (door closes)

27:21.182 --> 27:22.848
- Good.

27:22.892 --> 27:27.227
Um, Samantha, Lauren is a little
shy when it comes to boys,

27:27.271 --> 27:29.980
so I'd appreciate it if
you didn't pressure her.

27:30.024 --> 27:32.775
- Sorry, I was just
trying to help.

27:33.611 --> 27:34.401
- It's okay.

27:35.446 --> 27:38.405
- So, what's the plan?

27:38.449 --> 27:41.450
- Uh, well, I have a client
coming in a couple of minutes.

27:42.828 --> 27:44.536
- What do you do anyway?

27:44.580 --> 27:45.454
- I'm a psychologist.

27:45.498 --> 27:47.623
- Oh, wow, that's intense.

27:47.667 --> 27:50.876
- Um, it can be,
it's very rewarding.

27:50.920 --> 27:52.461
- Yeah.

27:52.505 --> 27:53.837
Do you wanna psychoanalyze
me? (chuckles)

27:53.881 --> 27:55.673
- No, no,

27:55.716 --> 27:58.425
but I would like to get to
know you a little better.

27:58.469 --> 28:00.761
- Yeah, I'd like to get
to know me better too.

28:02.139 --> 28:04.139
- Well, if you ever
wanna talk, I'm here.

28:04.183 --> 28:05.474
(doorbell rings)

28:05.518 --> 28:06.809
Oh, that's my client.

28:06.852 --> 28:08.769
Are you okay for a little while?

28:08.813 --> 28:10.938
- Yeah, I'm just gonna study.

28:10.981 --> 28:12.356
- Great.

28:12.400 --> 28:13.440
Uh, maybe we can
grab lunch later?

28:13.484 --> 28:15.234
- Yeah, that sounds good.

28:20.074 --> 28:22.825
(tense music)

28:22.868 --> 28:24.368
Katie: Heather, how you been?

28:24.412 --> 28:25.160
- Really well.

28:25.204 --> 28:27.496
Katie: Good, come on in.

28:29.333 --> 28:30.374
- It's been a good week.

28:30.418 --> 28:31.500
- Good.

28:31.544 --> 28:33.085
Buttons feeling any better?

28:33.129 --> 28:36.505
- Yes, Buttons is
feeling so much better.

28:36.549 --> 28:39.383
- Come on over here,
I'm all set up.

28:45.099 --> 28:47.433
(tense music)

28:58.195 --> 29:00.571
(pops hood)

29:37.359 --> 29:38.776
So, Tuesday, same time?

29:38.819 --> 29:42.154
- Yes, I'm putting
it in my calendar.

29:42.198 --> 29:42.988
- Heather?

29:44.200 --> 29:45.157
Is that you?

29:45.201 --> 29:46.116
(tense music)

29:46.160 --> 29:47.075
- Samantha, I--

29:47.119 --> 29:48.452
- It's been so long.

29:48.496 --> 29:50.454
Katie: Do you two
know each other?

29:50.498 --> 29:51.705
Samantha: Well, we
used to be friends,

29:51.749 --> 29:53.957
until she disappeared on me.

29:54.001 --> 29:55.751
- I gotta go.

29:57.129 --> 29:58.670
- Well, it was nice
to see you again.

30:00.132 --> 30:01.799
Katie: Heather, wait.

30:01.842 --> 30:03.675
Heather, Heather, talk to me.

30:03.719 --> 30:05.761
Heather, Heather,
what do you need?

30:05.805 --> 30:07.346
Talk to me, what do you need?

30:07.389 --> 30:08.263
- What is she doing here?

30:08.307 --> 30:08.972
Why would you have her here?

30:09.016 --> 30:10.724
- Who, Samantha?

30:10.768 --> 30:13.393
- I can't, I can't be here
anymore, I have to go!

30:13.437 --> 30:14.645
- Wait, that's the Sam?

30:23.030 --> 30:24.780
(knock at door)

30:24.824 --> 30:25.614
Hey.

30:25.658 --> 30:26.990
Samantha: Hey.

30:27.034 --> 30:28.325
- You still wanna
grab some lunch?

30:28.369 --> 30:29.117
- Yeah, sure.

30:30.371 --> 30:31.745
- So how do you know Heather?

30:33.582 --> 30:36.333
- Uh, I spent a lot of time
around here a while back.

30:36.377 --> 30:38.418
Did you know she's a
lifeguard at the beach?

30:39.672 --> 30:40.963
- Small world, isn't it?

30:43.342 --> 30:45.217
- I can't wait until
I see Heather again,

30:45.261 --> 30:49.429
we have so much to talk about.
(tense music)

30:51.767 --> 30:54.685
- So I was thinking
Lighthouse Cafe for lunch?

30:54.728 --> 30:56.270
Samantha: Yeah, I'm easy.

30:57.481 --> 30:58.230
- Great.

31:11.412 --> 31:13.787
So when does the
next semester start?

31:13.831 --> 31:15.998
- Um, in a couple of weeks.

31:16.041 --> 31:18.125
Katie: You excited to go back?

31:18.168 --> 31:19.835
- Yeah, I'm excited.

31:19.879 --> 31:20.919
Katie: It's always good

31:20.963 --> 31:21.837
to get back into
your old routine,

31:21.881 --> 31:23.046
it makes you feel normal again.

31:23.090 --> 31:24.715
- What, are you
saying I'm not normal?

31:24.758 --> 31:26.967
- No, no, no, I wasn't
saying that, I just--

31:27.011 --> 31:28.594
Samantha: (chuckles) I'm
just messing with you, Katie.

31:28.637 --> 31:29.845
(Katie chuckles)

31:29.889 --> 31:30.721
Katie: You know, I can help you

31:30.764 --> 31:32.264
with your studies if you want.

31:33.684 --> 31:36.560
- You, you have a PhD, right?

31:36.604 --> 31:39.730
- Yeah, I got it
after I had Tommy.

31:39.773 --> 31:40.731
(water sprays)
(car beeps)

31:40.774 --> 31:41.690
What the heck?

31:53.454 --> 31:54.870
Oh my.

31:54.914 --> 31:57.706
Oh, god, that cannot be good.

31:59.585 --> 32:00.584
Oh.

32:03.714 --> 32:05.172
- You have to, yeah.

32:07.301 --> 32:08.467
(Katie pops hood)

32:08.510 --> 32:10.969
(Katie groans)

32:13.724 --> 32:16.058
- (groans) This can't be good.

32:16.101 --> 32:18.685
Let me call Ryan, hold on, um...

32:19.980 --> 32:21.939
(tense music)

32:21.982 --> 32:24.608
Hey, Ry, yeah, it's me,
do you have a minute?

32:26.153 --> 32:29.613
I think my car is overheating,
I'm with Samantha.

32:29.657 --> 32:32.449
Uh, yeah, we're on Elkmont Road.

32:33.702 --> 32:34.993
Great.

32:35.037 --> 32:36.453
Thank you so much.

32:36.497 --> 32:37.871
Okay, yeah, we'll be here, bye.

32:40.334 --> 32:41.291
Okay.

32:41.335 --> 32:42.876
Um, Ryan's gonna come help.

32:42.920 --> 32:45.462
I am so sorry, I hope
you're not too hungry?

32:45.506 --> 32:47.172
- Oh, no, it's totally fine.

32:47.216 --> 32:50.676
That's so nice of Ryan to just
come running when you call.

32:50.719 --> 32:53.178
- Yeah, well, I'm useless
when it comes to cars.

32:53.222 --> 32:54.638
I leave that to
Ryan and your dad.

32:54.682 --> 32:55.847
Samantha: Mm-hmm.

32:58.394 --> 33:00.185
- Look, Samantha,

33:00.229 --> 33:02.854
Ryan and I have been
friends since junior high,

33:02.898 --> 33:03.814
I love your father.

33:05.150 --> 33:08.568
- Okay, did I say any different?

33:08.612 --> 33:12.656
- No, I just want you
to be able to trust me

33:12.700 --> 33:14.866
and know that I'm
here for you, okay?

33:14.910 --> 33:15.742
Whatever you need.

33:17.079 --> 33:19.371
- I had a mom, I don't
need another one.

33:24.670 --> 33:25.627
(Katie sighs)

